In a later version they can also answer the meal they ate and get the amount of calories they consumed.
In an even later version users can get the amount of calories that a user should eat based on some questions and get the amount of serving size per food group. Users can enter their mood before and after meals and get recommendations for next meal.

MVP features:
Login page
Selecting meal categories in pie chart on dropdown
Storing the user input data in a database
2.0 features:
Textual rendering of the food consumed
Calorie count with user entered meals using Nutritionix/USDA API
Links on category selection page with list of each food group to help user decide which category their food is in

3.0 features:

Do users want to know how much should be there ideal calorie intake? Second link is that of a calculation formula to implement to calculate the daily calorie intake of a person based on few parameters:
https://www.choosemyplate.gov/myplateplan
https://www.calculator.net/calorie-calculator.html
Is the user interested in the breakdown of how many servings of each food group they should consume based on the calorie intake? If yes there is a data chart with that breakdown that says the serving size per day of each food group and some eg of what constitutes that serving size for each food category.
https://www.calculator.net/calorie-calculator.html (Once you click submit it takes you to the page that displays serving size of each food group.
      3.   Track moods per meal and once enough date, give recommendations for next meal


API:
Nutritionix api: https://developer.nutritionix.com/docs/v1_1 (limitation on active users of 2, but for demo should work). It has an item description, calories and serving size.
Format of Response:
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1jZSa039OfpQOiRzaS980nPKCvVe2TRKRPZk7ZbaH7kE/edit#gid=0 
USDA API: https://ndb.nal.usda.gov/ndb/doc/index 
NDB (usda) api for calculation of calories of food items:(attached is the link to the response format for this)
http://api.nal.usda.gov/ndb/nutrients/?format=json&api_key=DEMO_KEY&nutrients=205&nutrients=204&nutrients=208&nutrients=269

